reviews.text: Such fantastic guides! They are so knowledgeable. The tour is fantastic and informative. The castle itself is an epic local find that's honestly a well kept secret. Learning about the history of the property and seeing the one of a kind architecture is so rewarding. I highly recommend anybody in the area interested in history, castles, architecture, or just a cool home come check this place out!

This place is an hidden gem in Bucks county. The guide was really nice and very professional. The castle is simply amazing, Henry Mercer was a true lover of the human nature and you can feel it by exploring the 44 rooms of his castle. The things that most impressed me are the clay tiles with cuneiform writings embedded in one of the Salon columns that are dated way before Christ.

This ultimate man-cave was built entirely of cement using construction methods developed on site. The docents are very knowledgeable and answered our many questions about the Moravian pottery and unique tiles adorning the interior of the structure. Each of the many hundreds of tiles had a story to tell. The museum contains artifacts from many places around the world.

This is an amazing place to visit and to think that it was one man's dream. I toured the place which I found very fascinating with the number of rooms and all the decorations. It is also a good place to do photography. I highly recommend this place if you are in the area.

We visited in winter, so the castle blended in with the sycamores as we walked up the long drive. The second the abode came into view, I knew we were in for a treat, and the basic tour that we booked last Sunday morning totally delivered ($15/adult, teachers in the tri-state area are free with school ID).
Our docent was very knowledgeable about the house's style and the craftsmanship that went into the design, and she was excited to show us all of the cool artifacts the owner had collected.
Parents, consider the following before booking: there is a strict no-touching policy. The tour lasts about an hour and you will be expected to keep up with the group the whole time.

Went with a group of ladies and had a wonderful time.  I bought a few souvenirs and was surprised when I got home that two cute wooden bookmarks I got were actually $7.50 each...I thought they were $.75!!!  Glad I only bought two.  Next time I will definitely pay closer attention when looking at prices!! LOL!!!   Chairs were on the agenda.. some were very distinctive and gorgeous!!! Well worth the visit!

I went with a school trip with my daughter. The trip was free and paid for by a sponsor. We had a great tour guide Dale a she was wonderful at keeping the kids attention and showing them painting she knew would interest them .
Really nice experience everyone was really nice. There was a jazz show held there also. There was a tour of the museum.

For a small Pennsylvania museum tucked away I'm historic Doylestown PA, I can say I was highly impressed. The layout, style and curation of it was pretty good. Although it's not what most art enthusiasts thing of when you say impressionism, they did a great job getting good works of art from only PA.  

My favorite was the exhibit of the creative mid century modern furniture pieces. How someone was able to make wood come together the way they did is extraordinary!

I'll show my favorite painting below.
Just a fabulous small museum with a big city feel. Great rotating exhibits and extra events. Easy parking and access. Programming for all ages.

it doesn't look like much on the outside but my 2yo had a blast! it's inexpensive, very close, and not overcrowded like Chuck E. Cheese. it could use a little sprucing up but overall we liked the place and will be going back
We had our 4 years old birthday party there today. the staff was great and very accommodating. We will definitely be back again.
Excellent place for kids. I have 3 kids 13y, 9y and 4y and all had a good time.

It's really the only place you can take toddlers and babies any day any time. Inexpensive, fun games, basic food but good enough. The staff leaves alot to be desired not friendly but not rude although I always feel like they are just waiting for us to leave. Never crowded. One of a kind. I'm glad they are there.  
I know confusing....
Kids love it and its affordable but let's be honest, they need a complete arcade overhaul.

Very Nice and cozy..don't really want to share my secret..lol.. seafood is off the chart.. incredible down home atmosphere..the people are very hospitable and listen to all your requests..best seafood on bucks county hands down..don't miss it trust me..
The did is consistently good and fresh. Good variety of food, I suggest you order greens and grains with chicken and spicy lamb

So the food was good. Slightly bland. Nothing jaw dropping but The restaurant is just too small. I was sitting elbow to elbow with a stranger at another table. Also the portions we average and expensive. I could go to Carrabas and spend less money. The way I see it mom and pop shops can be more expensive than chain restaurants but they have to offer higher quality food or service , more authentic dishes, better seasoning, a better environment or something to set them apart. As there front facade that is still unfinished after years of remodeling suggest they are close but have yet to reach the finish line. Maybe they will find a niche soon. Maybe the outside seating area will stop looking like a construction site soon. I’ve live here for 5 years and I’ve been saying maybe soon for longer than I should. But I feel they will either figure it out or go out of business. I’m rooting for them to win. Every year or so I try them again with high hopes.

This family owned restaurant was a recommendation and was delicious.  The environment is homey, the service quick and creme brulee pie was the best! Even better that there were friendly regulars and you can bring your own wine.

Italian seafood restaurant, very small it's best to make reservations, we order the specials it wasn't that great and higher than the menu options they don't have them written down so we didn't know till we got our $160 bill . We order buffalo scallops that had a weird texture something with the coating and shrimp and lump crab pasta with broccoli rabe , the broccoli was over cooked you can hard find any crab and 6 medium shrimp my son had a steak it was ok. Not worth the money it is a BYOB

This is a great place to go to watch the football match. If course, this is real football. If you call it the "S" sport, there is a swear jar. Also, they are happy to put in the rugby matches if you ask (amazing fur bars in the USA). Great pizza and wonderful draught beer selection. Definitely give this place a visit on game day.

Place blows. Place order at 5pm told will be at house between 530 -545pm. Call them at 6pm to ask were order is I am told on it's way. I reside 10min from villa caprice. Call again at 630pm ask were my order is told oh it's with driver he has multiple delivers. I just receive a phone call at 638pm we are making your order now. So sorry give us 30 min. There must be something wrong with the system. No we will refund you nothing. Never again.
Loved the atmosphere. Matt truly cares about his service and the customers. Great staff and food is top notch
Pizza is awesome! Staff is super nice! Been going here for years! Deck outside is great in the warmer weather!
Turned the best trattoria in the area into a sports bar. Tragic......don't bother auto apologizing either.

Great for families. 
I was a little hesitant going here, because the initial entryway was crowded and we had two children, but the experience was great both times we went. 
They have a children's menu, kids cups, boosters and high chairs. The service was quick, especially when she could tell we like to eat and run. 
The food was about a 3.8. No gourmet but good.  We got the kids burger and mac and cheese (both were eaten and enjoyed by the kids.) We also got a sandwich and a salad. Next time, I'll stay away from the salad and stick to a more bar-type item, I think I'll have better luck.
The next time we went, the power was out, so no food, but we got to hang on the back deck and get a beer. My son loves watching the trains come in, and a lot of the outdoor seating is covered, so I didnt need to worry about sunscreen. 
Overall, WE WILL BE BACK. I'd love to sit outside again and try some different food. 
Update pending. 🤞

The Station Taphouse, opened in March 2015 by the same owners as the Jamison Pour House, is a restaurant featuring a lot of craft beers on draft and in bottles. The menu is ample and food of high quality. They are very accommodating when it comes to hosting group events, myself having attended a number of family funeral luncheons at this restaurant over the years. If you are in the Doylestown area, it is worth a visit.

This is an upscale sports bar without the pretension.  Food is very good.  They have some unconventional fare as well as American staples.  And the wings are great.  Since it is an old rail station the ambiance is cool.
Good place to watch a game, solid beer menu, really good burgers and fries.  The chili is really good but very spicy.  The wait staff did a good job of taking care of us without being overbearing.

Overall very good, though it is really just tavern food. A step or two up from someplace like TGI Fridays. We ordered tacos which were very good, and fried Italian rice balls which were not quite warm in the middle. Good beer selection, and I do like the ambiance of the place.

EXCELLENT food very inventive. Love the tastes and textures. Variety is amazing too. Small plates which allows you to sample many foods. We went with 4 each of us ordered 3 plates and shared everything. Perfect service so very attentive to our needs. This is a place you come back to again and again. Love it. Great cocktails too.

We were disappointed in our dinner. We have eaten here many times and loved it but this was very different. Service as always was stellar. The wine was exceptional. Unfortunately the food was mediocre.  We started with salmon tacos and I'm still concerned that we,ll be sick from the aged salmon. The spinach quiche was excellent. It was mostly spinach and mushroom and the texture was perfect. The buffalo buffalo beef cake was hard to cut through, but the pickled celery was tasty. Next we had the potato skins.  These were very sloppy Joe's on half a baked potato.  The cheese tray was tasty but certainly not 16 dollars tasty for four sugar cubes of cheese. Overall the $180 price tag left us feeling like we should have gone elsewhere.

One of the best restaurants (possible the best) in Doylestown. I have no hesitation recommending them to anyone. While the menu is meat heavy, vegetarians and vegans will be happy to know that they have separate menus that contain variations to suit their dietary needs...you just need to ask. Other specialty menus may exist, but I didn't confirm this.

Honey Restaurant is a special place. Our server, Jason, was fabulous and explained all the different amazing mix of foods fully and understandably. He was fun, entertaing and added to a very enjoyable evening. ...all the way around Honey was definitely worth it!!! We will go back!
Quite an experience. All the menu is amazing. You won't regret anything.

Did the Hibachi dinner. It was pretty typical for performance. The food was excellent and there was a very generous portion provided and everyone ended up taking home at least enough for lunch the next day.
You don’t leave here hungry, and the prices are definitely reasonable. Will go back again! Great service from a waitress named Moriah! Very thorough with no slip ups!! Tipped well of course ! 👍
Their sushi is the best around.  Prices are high but you have to pay for quality fish.  The Shrimp Tempura is absolutely fantastic and I definitely recommend it

My family usually come here on special occasions like after graduation ceremony and birthdays dinner. Hibachi is everyone's choice and we enjoy watching the cook's  skillful performance with food  and interaction with us. It has been almost 20 years since late 1990s.... The food and service is consistently great and very entertaining.

Went here with local family while visiting the area. We didn't have reservations but were early enough to grab a lounge table. Ordered Lobster Dynamite, spicy tuna, and vegetable roll to share with my sister. The rolls were very well loaded and nothing was skimped. Green tea ice cream was two large scoops. Everything was excellently prepared and presented. I can see why the tables were full. Oishii!
Very tasty Indian food.  BYOB. Understaffed wait staff. Pleasant space. All of our party of 8 enjoyed their meal.
Went with a group with diverse tastes and everyone found something. All of the food was delicious.
Fresh ingredients cooked well. Nice atmosphere and staff.
1st time there. I don't know what to order. They suggested a nice meal and it was fantastic
The ambience, food, and service was all par excellence

One of my favorite restaurants. Impressive menu choices and I am never disappointed when navigating trying new things. Their happy hour deals are a must and the sushi is outstanding. If going for brunch definitely try the oyster shooters.

A group of friends and I went on Saturday night after hanging out in Doylestown for a bit. We were at the back bar for a good 2 hours and between everyone we spent around $600. The back bartender was great and we were all minding our business and hanging out within our group. We were all walking out to leave and one of the servers was sent over by the manager to us telling us we were being kicked out? He didn’t have any reasoning behind it other then he was told one of us fell (which is false) and that we could talk to the manager about it. When we asked the manager about it he was standing at the front with his arms crossed and a smug look on his face and wouldn’t even talk to us and just told us to get out. Glad to know you can spend tons of money at an establishment and still be treated so horrible. Will never be going back there and will never recommend.

went in with friends after a St.Patty's day crawl. The front Bartender couldn't have been any ruder.  clientele is snobby and rude as bartender. I have lived in this area for 20 years. will never go here again. I'll be sure to stick with the Mesquito Grille where they treat all their patrons with dignity . My review is the same as Jamie Rocks. apparently its normal there.
I like this place alot.  Its trendy, cool with a really nice crowd.  The food is great, friendly cute servers, efficient friendly bartenders, AND a gorgeous outdoor bar in season...go !

Surprisingly this Sushi / steak restaurant has fantastic vegetarian options. I enjoyed the Impossible Burger along with a Christmas-themed mule. The restaurant itself is beautiful.  A wee bit of Philadelphia in Doylestown!
One of our favorite places to eat in town. Good place to have a drink and listen to live music. Quieter scene than the dance club next door. Terrific food and large portions.

Found our regular haunt in Doylestown. Matt runs an excellent establishment.  Incredible menu that will appeal to just about everyone and the friendly atmosphere ensures a consistent experience. A great place to hang out. See Patrick at the bar for the best drinks imaginable.
Good food and service. Nice bright atmosphere. Many options on menu. Out of Miller light on tap but it is Christmas week. No complaints. 1st visit but wouldn’t hesitate come back.

This place has free poker tournaments on Tuesday Night at 8pm and real estate meetings on the last wednesday of every month. Love the food and the split bars. 2 bars in one is a very unique feature. Patrick and Morgan are terrific.
Great acoustic dead music, awesome band, good vibes...

1st time there. I don't know what to order. They suggested a nice meal and it was fantastic
The ambience, food, and service was all par excellence
Pretzle dogs are amazing! I once saw a jazz musician play the salty pretzel in here. I gave him a 5

Took my mother there to look around and she liked it! Even bought some homemade spaghetti to take home .. She is very fussy about food ( has to be fresh), so we will see. Used to make all her own pasta.... The kids still dream about it. So we will wait to hear back from her to see what she thinks. Martin loves their cheeses... And everything else in their! The spinach ravioli with sauce is one of my favorites

Very nice place. Full of Italian delights. Plenty of parking. Lots of choices
The sandwiches were okay. The pizza was good, a little tough.
I would give it another chance
We love this place! So much fantastic food to choose from! It's a wonderful adventure everything we go.
Hey, just go. If you want authentic, fresh, and a variety of Italian foods, Altomontes is the place. I can't say enough so I'll stop here - Just go! I guarantee you won't leave without a lot of food!

This place can't get an order correct even if it tried.  I stopped ordering from this place a long time ago because they would never give me the correct order.  However, today we ordered lunch for our client meeting (not my idea) only to find out that they gave us the wrong order. What made this even worse is that looking at the woman's order that they did give, showed that this place would have given her a completely wrong order as well!  This scenario happens way to often. To top it off, this place doesn't really care when you bring it to their attention.

Good coffee, gelato and ice cream. Sometimes their espresso is off and the machine needs to be adjusted. But most of the time they are on point. It's a small, comfortable place and has it's charm. Tough to find a seat when it's busy.
I really like the place. The stuff is really friendly. I love the gelato there, its amazing. I can highly recommend it.
Great hot coco on a cold day. A good amount of seating. Quick
Okay I'm more of a soft serve guy when it comes to icecream
Not crazy about it, my latte was average, milk not steamed well. Ok pastries, nice service.
Pizza was a 6.5, they threw it in the oven to give it a crisp. The local law enforcement likes the place so it's safe to grab a slice anytime. Seems like a staple there.

Nat's has been a neighborhood staple for as long as I can remember. They have the BEST wings, cheesesteaks, and of course PIZZA! Somehow it has such a unique flavor compared to the other pizza places around. I've had pizza from many places, including NYC, and Nat's is still the best I've ever had!

Sometimes you can have the best piece of pizza you've ever had and sometimes it can be the worst. Most of the time pizza is just pizza. That is the case with Nats. Been going to Nats for over 25 years now and the pizza is consistent but exactly the same as it was. Nothing special just a decent slice of pizza. Number one complaint would be way too much grease! Maybe better cheese not sure? Either way if you need a quick bite I would go but only as a last resort
Great food and pizza and will go back.
Ordered just wings, not only did they take about 10 minutes longer than was estimated they were undercooked and gross. Would not recommend

Not a "real" Primo location. I buy Primo Hoagies all the time, all over the area. This location does not use the same ingredients. Terrible service, rude employees. Do yourself a favor and go to the Primo location in Chalfont.
Unique sandwiches and very tasty rolls
great Italian hoagie. great bread always makes a great sandwich
To start, great hoagies; am partial to the Roast Beef Schwartzie and the Abruzzese. Have always had very good service at this location. Staff has been accommodating and pleasant.
Very friendly staff and fast service.

We were the only table at the restaurant when we sat down at 6 on a Friday.  We were seated and waited on by 4 different people.  The problem is that my wife's meal (chicken with a side of pasta - pasta being the main reason to eat here, and what she was most looking forward to) didn't come out when mine and my two sons' did.  Well, the chicken did, but not the pasta.  We promptly asked for it, and were told it was coming right out.  It wasn't.  It didn't come for at least another 15 minutes, delivered by someone else, at which time we were all finished and told him to just box it.  The waitress came back, oblivious to the fact that it wasn't on the table in front of us as we were getting ready to leave, even though we had reminded her earlier that we were waiting on it. 

Only other criticism - the wine pour is weak...maybe 4 oz.  For a generic $10 glass of white.

Food is decent, but just do takeout...
Enjoyed fantastic wood-oven pizza, many selections, all great. Service was also good.

It’s an ok place, however it really needs some serious renovations. The waitress was nice but had dirty nails ... we should have left just seing that....
The pastas were ok but far to be great... not going back.
Beautiful outdoor patio,  amazing food.   One of the best meals we have had in a long time.   The vegetarian lasagna was superb.
We were in Paganini today. The atmosphere is gloomy. Service is terrible and the staff extremely was rude. Just avoid this place.

One word AWFUL!!! Started off with a watered down vodka martini with mushy olives. I ordered chicken corn chowder soup which was watery and extremely salty. As an entree, I ordered fish tacos. The fish was over cooked (tasted like rubber) and over seasoned. I couldn’t even get through a whole taco. So, I ordered grilled cheese off the menu because how can anyone muck that up....wrong. It was all bread hardly any cheese and the cheese wasn’t even melted all the way through. Very disappointing lunch and will not go back. I can go elsewhere and spend less money where the food is 100 times better.

Food was excellent, service was average but the manager did come over and introduce himself and checked if we needed anything. The atmosphere was very cozy. I had the lemon thyme chicken and my girlfriend had the arugula pesto pasta. Both dishes were good sized portions and very tasty. Prices were fair. Would definitely dine here again and would recommend to anyone looking for a good dining experience in the area.

We had an awesome dinner!  Our server, Julia, was very knowledgeable about the menu and the gluten free options . My wife feels very confident eating here with her gluten allergy.
Thank you, Mr manager for the side of wild rice!
Definitely in our dinner rotation!

We've been here a few times and had varying levels of food and service.

They're currently doing half price vouchers on local flavor which we used. So it makes the food pretty reasonable .

I ordered a cheese steak. Standard fayre and hard to get wrong, but it was good.

My daughter has a dairy allergy and they failed on 2 points. I asked for the fries with the cheesesteak to be on a different plate to the cheesesteak so no cheese went on them, wasn't done.
They also brought her food with a tub of cheese on the plate.

We made it very clear about the allergies and were not impressed.

We do have another voucher so will go again and use it but it's not close to being our go to place which is a shame because the location and the building are lovely

My boyfriend had raw food served to him and when we sent it back not only were we charged for the second plate as well but the waitress had an attitude when we asked to send it back. I had a salad and somehow I managed to get food poisoning. I saw multiple members of the staff including my waitress smoking outside,  so I was not surprised that my food reeked of cigarettes.

When we were trying to eat our food we were rudely interrupted not only by loud and rude customers at the bar, we observed very rude and hostile comments made between workers. Noticed a higher up, possibly a manager, flirting with one of his worker, WHAT!!!

I needed a drink after this awful experience so we went to the high tops near the bar. We were rudely kicked out of this spot by bussers setting up for brunch.

Awful experience on already overpriced food would not recommend. Prison serves better food than this.
One of our favorite places to eat in town. Good place to have a drink and listen to live music. Quieter scene than the dance club next door. Terrific food and large portions.

Good food and service. Nice bright atmosphere. Many options on menu. Out of Miller light on tap but it is Christmas week. No complaints. 1st visit but wouldn’t hesitate come back.
